* This POJO represents the {@link * TestAdSelectionManager#overrideAdSelectionFromOutcomesConfigRemoteInfo} ( * AddAdSelectionOverrideRequest, Executor, OutcomeReceiver)} request * *

It contains, a {@link AdSelectionFromOutcomesConfig} which will serve as the identifier for * the specific override, a {@code String} selectionLogicJs and {@code String} selectionSignals * field representing the override value *

methods.name: public AdSelectionFromOutcomesConfig getAdSelectionFromOutcomesConfig()
methods.comment:
* @return an instance of {@link AdSelectionFromOutcomesConfig}, the configuration of the ad
     *     selection process. This configuration provides the data necessary to run Ad Selection
     *     flow that generates bids and scores to find a wining ad for rendering.

methods.name: public String getOutcomeSelectionLogicJs()
methods.comment:
* @return The override javascript result, should be a string that contains valid JS code. The
     *     code should contain the outcome selection logic that will be executed during ad outcome
     *     selection.

methods.name: public AdSelectionSignals getOutcomeSelectionTrustedSignals()
methods.comment:
* @return The override trusted scoring signals, should be a valid json string. The trusted
     *     signals would be fed into the outcome selection logic during ad outcome selection.
